1. One hundred and sixty-five patients were included in the study.
2. These patients had low-energy intertrochanteric fractures.
3. The fractures were classified as AO/OTA 31A.
4. The patients were included during a 2-year period.
5. The 2-year period was from 2005 to 2006.
6. The inclusion of patients was done prospectively.
